 <H1>Summary</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Concurrency control and recovery are among the most important functions provided by a DBMS.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Users need not worry about concurrency.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>System automatically inserts lock/unlock requests and schedules actions of different Xacts in such a way as to ensure that the resulting execution is equivalent to executing the Xacts one after the other in some order.
<LI>Write-ahead logging (WAL) is used to undo the actions of aborted transactions and to restore the system to a consistent state after a crash.
<LI>Consistent state:  Only the effects of commited Xacts seen.</UL></UL></P>

